  <titles>
    <title type="short" as="introduced">Congressional and Judicial Equal Employment Opportunity Act of 1988</title>
    <title type="official" as="introduced">A bill to amend title VII of the Civil Rights Act of 1964 to prohibit discrimination based on race, color, religion, sex, handicap, national origin, or age in employment in the legislative or judicial branches of the Federal Government; and to establish the Employment Review Board composed of senior Federal judges, which shall have authority to adjudicate claims regarding such discrimination.</title>
